 ity deserve a proper celebration. Join the Greater Durham Chamber of Comme
 rce as we cut the ribbon with Jewelsmith in honor of their Golden Era 50th
  Anniversary\, a milestone that belongs as much to Durham as it does to th
 e store itself. This isn't just a ribbon cutting. It's a homecoming. A Dur
 ham native\, Linda McGill founded Jewelsmith with a vision rooted deeply i
 n this city's spirit. Long before Durham became recognized as the creative
 \, artist-driven hub it is today\, Linda saw it coming. She believed this 
 city had a soul\, one that valued handcraft\, originality\, and the kind o
 f beauty that can't be mass-produced. Jewelsmith isn’t just a jewelry st
 ore. It’s an expression of that belief. Though Linda has since passed\, 
 her legacy lives on in the most meaningful way possible\, in the hands of 
 the employees she trusted to carry it forward. This celebration is for her
